PrecisOrder which provides authority (a) for the National Capital Commission to grant two Easements (ES-720-3) to Ontario Hydro for the installation, operation, etc., of two 500 kV electrical power transmission lines (75 years) and the relocation of one 44 kV line (49 years) across four strips of land situate on opposite sides of the Rideau River in the Cities of Nepean and Ottawa, in the Province of Ontario; and (b) for the revocation of Order in Council P.C.1989-4/182 of February 9, 1989.
